obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (15772)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15772&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Central Industrial`
  line `Security Force Act, 1968.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 10th March, 1969, vide notification No. S.O. 924, dated 3rd March, 1969, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (15773)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15773&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line ^1
  line `(a) "Director-General" means the Director-General of the Force appointed under section 4;`
  line
  line `(aa) "enrolled member of the Force" means any subordinate officer, under officer or any other`
  line `member of the Force of a rank lower than that of an under officer;`
  line
  line `(ab) "Force" means the Central Industrial Security Force constituted under section 3;`
  line
  line `(ac) "Force custody" means the arrest or confinement of a member of the Force in accordance`
  line `with rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "industrial undertaking" means any undertaking pertaining to a scheduled industry and`
  line `includes an undertaking engaged in any other industry, or in any trade, business or service which may`
  line `be regulated by Parliament by law;`
  line
  line `(c) "industrial undertaking in public sector" means an industrial undertaking owned, controlled or`
  line `managed by`
  line
  line `(i) a Government company as defined in section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956),`
  line
  line `(ii) a corporation established by or under a Central, Provincial or State Act, which is`
  line `controlled or managed by the Government;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(ca) "industrial establishment" means an industrial undertaking or a company as defined under`
  line `section 3 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956),or a firm registered under section 59 of the Indian`
  line `Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932),which is engaged in any industry, or in any trade, business or`
  line service;]
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(cb) "joint venture" means a venture jointly undertaken by the Central Government or State`
  line `Government with private industrial undertaking;]`
  line
  line ^4
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(e) "Managing Director", in relation to an industrial undertaking, means the person (whether`
  line `called a managing agent, general manager, manager, chief executive officer or by any other name)`
  line `who exercises control over the affairs of that undertaking;`
  line
  line `(f) "members of the Force" means a person appointed to the Force under this Act`
  line
  line ^5
  line `* * *;`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line ^6
  line `['(ga) "private industrial undertaking" means an industry owned, controlled or managed by a`
  line `person other than the Central or State Government or any industrial undertaking in public sector;']`
  line
  line `(h) "scheduled industry" means any industry engaged in the manufacture or production of the`
  line `articles mentioned in the First Schedule to the Industries (Development and Regulation) Act, 1951`
  line `(65 of 1951);`
  line
  line ^7
  line `['(ha) "subordinate officer" means a person appointed to the Force as an Inspector, a SubInspector`
  line `or an Assistant Sub-Inspector;';]`
  line
  line `(i) "supervisory officer" means any of the officers appointed under section 4 and includes any`
  line `other officer appointed by the Central Government as a supervisory officer of the Force.`
  line
  line ^7
  line `['(j) "under officer" means a person appointed to the Force as a Head Constable, Naik or Lance`
  line `Naik.']`
  line
  line ^8
  line `[(2) Any reference in this Act to a law which is not in force in any area shall, in relation to that area,`
  line `be construed as a reference to the corresponding law, if any, in force in that area.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 1983, s. 3, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 40 of 1999, s. 3 (w.e.f. 29-12-1999).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 22 of 2009, s. 2 (w.e.f. 10-1-2009).`
  line
  line `4. Clause (d) omitted by Act 14 of 1983, s. 3 (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  line
  line `5. The words ",other than a supervisory officer" omitted by Act 14 of 1983, s. 3 (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 22 of 2009, s. 2 (w.e.f. 10-1-2009).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 14 of 1983, s. 3 (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 15-6-1983)`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (15774)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15774&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted and maintained by the Central`
  line `Government ^1`
  line `[an armed force of the Union] to be called the Central Industrial Security Force for the`
  line `better protection and security of industrial undertakings owned by that Government^2`
  line `[,joint venture or`
  line `private industrial undertaking]`
  line ^3
  line `[and to perform such other duties as may be entrusted to it by the`
  line `Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Force shall be constituted in such manner, shall consist of such number of ^4`
  line [supervisory
  line `officers, subordinate officers, under officers and other enrolled] members of the Force who shall receive`
  line `such pay and other remuneration as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "a Force" (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 22 of 2009, s. 3 (w.e.f. 10-1-2009).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 40 of 1999, s. 4 (w.e.f. 29-12-1999).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 14 of 1983, s. 4, for "supervisory officers and members" (w.e.f. 15-6-1983)`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (15775)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Appointment and powers of supervisory officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15775&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) The Central Government may appoint a`
  line `a person to be the Director-General of the Force and such other supervisory officers as considered`
  line necessary.]
  line
  line `(2) The ^2[Director-General] and every other supervisory officer so appointed shall have, and may`
  line `exercise, such powers and authority as is provided by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2009, s. 4, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 10-1-2009).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 1983, s. 5, for "Inspector-General" (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (15776)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Appointment of enrolled members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 15-6-1983)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15776&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The^1[appointment of the enrolled members of`
  line `the Force shall rest with the Director-General] who shall exercise that power in accordance with rules`
  line `made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the power of appointment under this section may also be exercised by such other`
  line `supervisory officer as the Central Government may by order specify in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (15777)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Certificates of enrolled members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15777&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Every enrolled member of the Force shall`
  line `receive on his appointment a certificate in the form specified in the Schedule, under the seal of the`
  line `Director-General or such other supervisory officer as the Director-General may specify in this behalf, by`
  line `virtue of which the person holding such certificate shall be vested with the powers of an enrolled member`
  line `of the Force.]`
  line
  line `(2) Such certificate shall cease to have effect whenever the person named in it ceases for any reason`
  line `to be ^2[an enrolled member] of the Force.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "a member" (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (15778)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Superintendence and administration of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15778&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) The superintendence of Force shall`
  line `vest in the Central Government, and subject thereto and to the provisions of this Act and of any rules`
  line `made thereunder, the command, supervision and administration of the Force shall vest in the DirectorGeneral.]`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), the administration of the Force within such local`
  line `limits as may be prescribed shall be carried on by ^2`
  line `[such other supervisory officers as considered`
  line `necessary] in accordance with the provisions of this Act and of any rules made thereunder and every`
  line `supervisory officer placed in charge of the protection and security of an industrial undertaking^3`
  line [,joint
  line `venture or private industrial undertaking] shall, subject to any directions that may be given by the`
  line ^4
  line `[Central Government or the Director-General] in this behalf, discharge his functions under the general`
  line `supervision, direction and control of the Managing Director of that undertaking.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 1983. s. 8, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2009, s. 5, for certain words (w.e.f. 10-1-2009).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. bys. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2009).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 14 of 1983, s. 8, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (15779)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Dismissal, removal, etc., of members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15779&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of article 311 of`
  line `the Constitution and to such rules as the Central Government may make under this Act, any supervisory`
  line `officer may—`
  line
  line `(i)dismiss, ^1`
  line [remove]^2
  line `[, order for compulsory retirement of] or reduce in rank any ^3`
  line [enrolled
  line `member] of the Force whom he thinks remiss or negligent in the discharge of his duty, or unfit for`
  line `the same; or`
  line
  line `(ii) award any one or more of the following punishments to any ^3`
  line `[enrolled member] of the Force`
  line `who discharges his duty in a careless or negligent manner, or who by any act of his own renders`
  line `himself unfit for the discharge thereof, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) fine to any amount not exceeding seven day's pay or reduction in pay scale;`
  line
  line `(b) drill, extra guard, fatigue or other duty;`
  line
  line `(c) removal from any office of distinction or deprivation of any special emolument;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(d) withholding of increment of pay with or without cumulative effect;`
  line
  line `(e) withholding of promotion;`
  line
  line `(f) censure.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1989, s. 3, for "suspend" (w.e.f. 18-5-1989).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 40 of 1999, s. 5 (w.e.f. 29-12-1999).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 1983, s. 13 and the Schedule, for "member" (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (15780)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Appeal and revision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15780&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any^1[enrolled member] of the Force aggrieved by an order made`
  line `under section 8 may, within thirty days from the date on which the order is communicated to him, prefer`
  line `an appeal against the order to such authority as may be prescribed, and ^2`
  line `[subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (2A), sub-section (2B) and sub-section (3)], the decision of the said authority thereon shall be`
  line `final:`
  line
  line `Provided that the prescribed authority may entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `thirty days, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal in`
  line time.
  line
  line `(2) In disposing of an appeal, the prescribed authority shall follow such procedure as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(2A) Any enrolled member of the Force aggrieved by an order passed in appeal under`
  line `sub-section (1) may, within a period of six months from the date on which the order is communicated to`
  line `him, prefer a revision petition against the order to such authority as may be prescribed and in disposing of`
  line `the revision petition, the said authority shall follow such procedure as may be prescribed`
  line
  line `(2B) The authority, as may be prescribed for the purpose of this sub-section, on a revision petition`
  line `preferred by an aggrieved enrolled member of the Force or suomoto, may call for, within a prescribed`
  line `period, the records of any proceeding under section 8 or sub-section (2) or sub-section (2A) and such`
  line `authority may, after making inquiry in the prescribed manner, and subject to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `pass such order thereon as it thinks fit.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may call for and examine the record of any proceeding ^4`
  line `[under section 8,`
  line `8, sub-section (2), sub-section (2A) or sub-section (2B)] of this section and may make such inquiry or`
  line `cause such inquiry to be made and subject to the provisions of this Act, may pass such order thereon as it`
  line `thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order imposing an enhanced penalty under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) shall be`
  line `made unless a reasonable opportunity of being heard has been given to the person affected by such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 1983, s. 13 and the Schedule, for "member" (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 40 of 1999, s. 6, for "subject to the provisions of sub-section (3)"(w.e.f. 29-12-1999).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 29-12-1999).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 40 of 1999, s. 6, for "under section 8 or under sub-section (2)" (w.e.f. 29-12-1999)`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (15781)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Duties of members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15781&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of every ^1`
  line `*** member of the Force`
  line
  line `(a) promptly to obey and execute all orders lawfully issued to him by his superior authority;`
  line
  line `(b) to protect and safeguard the industrial undertakings owned by the Central Government`
  line `together with such other installations as are specified by that Government to be vital for the carrying`
  line `on of work in those undertakings, situate within the local limits of his jurisdiction:`
  line
  line `Provided that before any installation not owned or controlled by the Central Government is so`
  line `specified, the Central Government shall obtain the consent of the Government of the state in which`
  line `such installation is situate;`
  line
  line `(c) to protect and safeguard ^2[any joint venture, private industrial undertaking and] such other`
  line `industrial undertakings and installations for the protection and security of which he is deputed under`
  line `section 14;`
  line
  line `^3[(d) to protect and safeguard the employees of the industrial undertakings and installations`
  line `referred to in clauses (b) and (c);`
  line
  line `(e) to do any other act conducive to the better protection and security of the industrial`
  line `undertakings and installations referred to in clauses (b) and (c) and the employees referred to in`
  line `clause (d).]`
  line
  line `^4[(f) to provide technical consultancy services relating to security of any private sector industrial`
  line `establishments under section 14A;`
  line
  line `(g) to protect and safeguard the organisations owned or funded by the Government and the`
  line `employees of such organisations as may be entrusted to him by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(h) any other duty ^2[within and outside India] which may be entrusted to him by the Central`
  line `Government from time to time.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "supervisory officer and" omitted by Act 14 of 1983, s. 13 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 22 of 2009, s. 6 (w.e.f. 10-1-2009).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 1989, s. 4, for clause (d) (w.e.f. 18-5-1989).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 40 of 1999, s. 7 (w.e.f. 29-12-1999)`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (15782)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power to arrest without warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15782&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) Any member of the Force may, without any order from`
  line `from a Magistrate and without a warrant, arrest—`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(i) any person who voluntarily causes hurt to, or attempts voluntarily to cause hurt to, or`
  line `wrongfully restrains or attempts wrongfully to restrain or assaults, threatens to assault, or uses, or`
  line `threatens or attempts to use, criminal force to any employee, referred to in clause (d) of section 10, or`
  line `to him or any other member of the Force, in discharge of his duty as such employee or in execution of`
  line `his duty as such member, as the case may be, or with intent to prevent or to deter him from discharging his duty as such member, or in consequence of anything done or attempted to be done by`
  line `him in the lawful discharge of his duty as such member;]`
  line
  line `(ii) any person who has been concerned in, or against whom a reasonable suspicion exists of his`
  line `having been concerned in, or who is found taking precautions to conceal his presence under`
  line `circumstances which afford reason to believe that he is taking such precautions with a view to`
  line `committing,a cognizable offence which relates to property belonging to, or in the premises of, any`
  line `industrial undertaking referred to in clauses (b) and (c) of section 10, or relates to the other`
  line `installations, or to property in the premises of the other installations, referred to in those clauses;`
  line
  line `(iii) any person who commits or attempts to commit a cognizable offence which involves or`
  line `which is likely to involve ^3`
  line `*** danger to the life of any person engaged in carrying on any work`
  line `relating to any undertaking or installations referred to in clauses (b) and (c) of section 10.]`
  line
  line `(2) If any person is found trespassing on the premises of any industrial undertaking referred to in`
  line `clauses (b) and (c) of section 10, he may, without prejudice to any other proceedings which may be taken`
  line `against him, he removed from such premises by any ^4`
  line `*** member of the Force.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 1983, s. 9, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1989, s. 5, for clause (i) (w.e.f. 18-5-1989).`
  line
  line `3. The word "imminent" omitted by Act 20 of 1989, s. 5 (w.e.f. 18-5-1989).`
  line
  line `4. The words "supervisory officer or" omitted by Act 14 of 1983, s. 9 (w.e.f. 15-6-1983)`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (15783)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to search without warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15783&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever ^1`
  line `*** any member of the Force, not below the`
  line `the prescribed rank, has reason to believe that any such offence as is referred to in section 11 has been or`
  line `is being committed and that a search warrant cannot be obtained without affording the offender an`
  line `opportunity of escaping or of concealing evidence of the offence, he may detain the offender and search`
  line `his person and belongings forthwith and, if he thinks proper, arrest any person whom he has reason to`
  line `believe to have committed the offence.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of the ^2`
  line `[Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)] relating to searches under`
  line `that Code shall, so far as may be, apply to searches under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "any supervisory officer, or" omitted by s. 13 and The Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 13 and the Schedule, ibid., for "Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898)" (w.e.f. 15-6-1983)`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (15784)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Procedure to be followed after arrest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. The words "supervisory officer or" omitted by s. 13 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-6-1983)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15784&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Any ^1`
  line `*** member of the Force making an arrest under`
  line `this Act, shall, without unnecessary delay, make over the person so arrested to a police officer, or, in the`
  line `absence of a police officer, take such person or cause him to be taken to the nearest police station together`
  line `with a report of the circumstances occasioning the arrest.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (15785)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Deputation of the Force to industrial undertakings in public sector, joint venture or private sector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15785&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1(1) Subject to any general directions which may be issued by the Central Government,`
  line `it shall be lawful for the ^2`
  line `[Director-General], on a request received in this behalf from the`
  line `Managing Director concerned of an industrial undertaking in public sector^1`
  line `[, joint venture or private`
  line `sector], showing the necessity thereof, to depute such number of ^3`
  line `*** members of the Force as the`
  line ^2
  line `[Director-General] may consider necessary for the protection and security of that industrial undertaking`
  line `and any installations attached thereto and the ^4`
  line `*** members of the Force so deputed shall be at the charge`
  line `charge of the Managing Director:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of an undertaking, owned, controlled or managed,`
  line
  line `(i) by a Government company of which the Central Government is not a member;`
  line
  line `(ii) by a corporation established by or under a Provincial or State Act,`
  line
  line `no such request shall be entertained unless it is made with the consent of the Government of the State in`
  line `which the undertaking is situate.`
  line
  line `(2) If the ^2`
  line `[Director-General] is of the opinion that circumstances necessitating the deputation of the`
  line ^4
  line `*** members of the Force in relation to an industrial undertaking under sub-section (1) have ceased to`
  line `exist, or for any other reason it is necessary so to do, he may, after informing the Managing Director of`
  line `that industrial undertaking, withdraw the ^4`
  line `*** members of the Force so deputed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Managing Director may, on giving ^5`
  line `[threemonth's notice] in writing to the`
  line ^6
  line `[Director-General] require that the ^7`
  line `*** members of the Force so deputed shall be withdrawn, and the`
  line `Managing Director shall be relieved from the charge from the date of expiration of such notice or from`
  line `any earlier date on which the Force is so withdrawn.`
  line
  line `(3) Every ^8`
  line `*** member of the Force, while discharging his functions during the period of deputation,`
  line `shall continue to exercise the same powers and be subject to the same responsibilities, discipline and`
  line `penalties as would have been applicable to him under this Act, if he had been discharging those functions`
  line `in relation to an industrial undertaking owned by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2009, s. 7(w.e.f. 10-1-2009).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 1983, s. 13 and the Schedule, for "Inspector-General" (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  line
  line `3. The words "supervisory officers and" omitted by s. 13 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  line
  line `4. The words "officers and" omitted by s. 13 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 22 of 2009, s. 7, for "one month's notice" (w.e.f. 10-1-2009).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 14 of 1983, s. 13 and the Schedule, for "Inspector-General" (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  line
  line `7. The words "officers and" omitted by s. 13 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  line
  line `8. The words officer and omitted by s. 13 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_a:
  sectionId (15786)
  sectionNo 14A
  orderNo 15
  title `Technical Consultancy Service to industrial establishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1999, s. 8 (w.e.f. 29-12-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15786&sectionno=14A&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[14A. Technical Consultancy Service to industrial establishments.—(1) Subject to any general`
  line `directions which may be issued by the Central Government, it shall be lawful for the Director-General, on`
  line `a request received from the Managing Director of an industrial establishment in the private sector or any`
  line `other person authorised by him in this behalf, to direct the members of the Force to provide technical`
  line `consultancy services relating to security, to such industrial establishments in such manner and on payment`
  line `of such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The fee received under sub-section (1) shall be credited to the Consolidated Fund of India.`
  line
  line `Explanation—.For the purposes of this section, the expression "Managing Director", in relation to an`
  line `industrial establishment, means the person (whether called general manager, manager, chief executive`
  line `officer or a partner of a firm or by any other name) who exercises control over the affairs of the`
  line establishment.]
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (15787)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Officers and members of the Force to be considered always on duty and liable to be employed anywhere in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15787&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every ^1`
  line `*** member of the Force shall, for the purpose of this Act, be`
  line `be considered to be always on duty, and shall, at any time, be liable to be employed at any place`
  line within^2
  line `[or outside] India.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as provided in section 14, no ^3`
  line `*** member of the force shall engage himself in any`
  line `employment or office other than his duties under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "supervisory officer and" omitted by Act 14 of 1983, s. 13 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 22 of 2009, s. 8 (w.e.f. 10-1-2009).`
  line
  line `3. The words "supervisory officer or" omitted by Act 14 of 1983, s. 13 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-6-1983)`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (15788)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 17
  title `Restrictions respecting right to form association, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15788&sectionno=15A&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[15A. Restrictions respecting right to form association, etc.—(1) No member of the Force shall,`
  line `without the previous sanction in writing of the Central Government or of the prescribed authority,—`
  line
  line `(a) be a member of, or be associated in any way with, any trade union, labour union, political`
  line `association or with any class of trade unions, labour unions or political associations; or`
  line
  line `(b) be a member of, or be associated in any way with, any other society, institution, association or`
  line `organisation that is not recognised as part of the Force or is not of a purely social, recreatinonal or`
  line `religious nature; or`
  line
  line `(c) communicate with the press or publish or cause to be published any book, letter or other`
  line `document except where such communication or publication is in the bona fide discharge of his duties`
  line `or is of a purely literary, artistic or scientific character or is of a prescribed nature.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—If any question arises as to whether any society, institution, association or`
  line `organisation is of a purely social, recreational or religious nature under clause (b) of this sub-section`
  line `the decision of the Central Government thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(2) No member of the Force shall participate in, or address, any meeting or take part in any`
  line `demonstration organised by anybody or persons for any political purposes or for such other purposes as`
  line `may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (15789)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Responsibilities of members of the Force during suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15789&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `A member of the Force shall`
  line `not by reason of his suspension from office cease to be a member of the Force; and he shall, during that`
  line `period, be subject to the same responsibilities, discipline and penalties to which he would have been`
  line `subject if he were on duty.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (15790)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Surrender of certificate, arms, etc., by persons ceasing to be members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15790&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Every person who for any reason ceases to be ^1`
  line `[an enrolled member] of the Force, shall forthwith`
  line `surrender to any supervisory officer empowered to receive the same, his certificate of appointment, the`
  line `arms, accoutrements, clothing and other articles which have been furnished to him for the performance of`
  line `duties as ^1`
  line `[an enrolled member] of the Force.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who wilfully neglects or refuses to surrender his certificate of appointment or the`
  line `arms, accoutrements, clothing and other articles furnished to him, as required by sub-section (1), shall, on`
  line `conviction, be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one month, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to two hundred rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to apply to any article which, under the orders of the`
  line ^2
  line `[Director-General], has become the property of the person to whom the same was furnished.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 1983, s. 13 and the Schedule, for "a member" (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 13 and the Schedule, ibid., for "Inspector-General" (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (15791)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Penalties for neglect of duty, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 11,ibid., for sub-sections (1) and (2) (w.e.f. 15-6-1983)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15791&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in section`
  line `section 8, every member of the Force who shall be guilty of any violation of duty or wilful breach or`
  line `neglect of any rule or regulation or lawful order made by a supervisory officer, or who shall withdraw`
  line `from the duties of his office without permission, or who, being absent on leave, fails, without reasonable`
  line `cause, to report himself for duty on the expiration of the leave, or who engages himself without authority`
  line `in any employment other than his duty as a member of the Force, or who shall be guilty of cowardice,`
  line `may be taken into Force custody and shall, on conviction, be punished with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to one year.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), an`
  line `offence punishable under this section shall be cognizable and non-bailable.`
  line
  line `(2A) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the`
  line `Central Government may invest the Commandant with the powers of a Magistrate of any class for the`
  line `purpose of inquiring into or trying any offence committed by an enrolled member of the Force and`
  line `punishable under this Act, or any offence committed by an enrolled member of the Force against the`
  line `person or property of another member of the Force:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(i) when the offender is on leave or absent from duty; or`
  line
  line `(ii) when the offence is not connected with the offender's duties as an enrolled member of the`
  line `Force; or`
  line
  line `(iii) when it is a petty offence even if connected with the offender's duties as an enrolled member`
  line `of the Force; or`
  line
  line `(iv) when, for reasons to be recorded in writing, it is not practicable for the Commandant invested`
  line `with the powers of a Magistrate to inquire into or try an offence,`
  line
  line `the offence may, if the prescribed authority within the limits of whose jurisdiction the offence has been committed so requires, be inquired into or tried by an ordinary criminal court having jurisdiction in the matter.]`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in this section shall be construed to prevent any member of the Force from being prosecuted under any other law for any offence made punishable by that law, or for being liable under any such law to any other or higher penalty or punishment than is provided for such offence by this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be punished twice for the same offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (15792)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 21
  title `Application of Act 22 of 1922 to officers and members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. The words "supervisory officers and" omitted by Act 14 of 1983, s. 13 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15792&sectionno=19&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Police (Incitement`
  line `to Disaffection) Act, 1922, shall apply to ^1`
  line `*** members of the Force as it applies to members of a police`
  line force.
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (15793)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 22
  title `Certain Acts not to apply to members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15793&sectionno=20&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in the Payment of`
  line `Wages Act, 1936 (4 of 1936), or the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or the Factories Act,`
  line `1948 (63 of 1948), or any corresponding law relating to investigation and settlement of industrial disputes`
  line `in force in a State shall apply to members of the Force.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (15794)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 23
  title `Protection of acts of officers and members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. The words "supervisory officer or" omitted by s. 13 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-6-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15794&sectionno=21&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any suit or proceeding against`
  line `any ^1`
  line `*** member of the Force for any act done by him in the discharge of his duties, it shall be lawful for`
  line `him to plead that such act was done by him under the orders of a competent authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such plea may be proved by the production of the order directing the act, and if it is so`
  line `proved, the ^1`
  line `*** member of the Force shall thereupon be discharged from any liability in respect of the`
  line `act so done by him, notwithstanding any defect in the jurisdiction of the authority which issued such`
  line order.
  line
  line `(3) Nothwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, any legal`
  line `proceeding, whether civil or criminal, which may lawfully be brought against any ^1`
  line `*** member of the`
  line `Force for anything done or intended to be done under the powers conferred by, or in pursuance of, any`
  line `provision of this Act or the rules thereunder shall be commenced within three months after the act`
  line `complained of shall have been committed and not otherwise; and notice in writing of such proceeding and`
  line `of the cause thereof shall be given to the person concerned and his supervisory officer at least one month`
  line `before the commencement of such proceeding.`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (15795)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389&sectionId=15795&sectionno=22&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00009_196850_1517807320389
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for`
  line
  line `(a) regulating the classes, ranks, grades, pay any remuneration of ^1`
  line `*** members of the Force and`
  line `their conditions of service in the Force;`
  line
  line `(b) regulating the powers and duties of ^1`
  line `*** members of the Force authorised to exercise any`
  line `functions by or under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) fixing the period of service for ^1`
  line `*** members of the Force;`
  line
  line `(d) prescribing the description and quantity of arms, accoutrements, clothing and other necessary`
  line `articles to be furnished to the members of the Force;`
  line
  line `(e) prescribing the places of residence of members of the Force;`
  line
  line `(f) institution, management and regulation of any fund for any purpose connected with the`
  line `administration of the Force;`
  line
  line `(g) regulating the punishments and prescribing authorities to whom appeals shall be preferred`
  line `from orders of punishment, or remission of fines or other punishments, and the procedure to be`
  line `followed for the disposal of such appeals;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(gg) regulating matters with respect to Force custody under this Act including the procedure to`
  line `be followed for taking persons into such custody;`
  line
  line `(ggg) regulating matters with respect to disposal of cases relating to offences under this Act and`
  line `specifying the places in which persons convicted under this Act may be confined;c9563`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(gggg) prescribing authority under sub-section (2A) of section 9 and the procedure to be`
  line `followed by such authority in disposing of the revision petition;`
  line
  line `(ggggg) prescribing authority under sub-section (2B) of section 9, the period within which such`
  line `authority may call for the records and the manner in which such authority may make inquiry;]i`
  line
  line `(h) the terms and conditions subject to which ^4`
  line `*** members of the Force may be deputed under`
  line `section 14 and the charges therefor; ^5`
  line ***
  line
  line ^6
  line `[(hh) the manner in which and the fee on payment of which the technical consultancy`
  line `services shall be provided under sub-section (1) of section 14A; and]`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed ^7`
  line `[or in respect of which rules are`
  line `required to be made under this Act.]`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days, which may be comprised in one`
  line `session ^8`
  line `[or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive session aforesaid], both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule, or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be ; so however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
